1
00:01:53,122 --> 00:01:54,650
马德·德·迪奥斯。
Madre de Dios.

2
00:01:55,674 --> 00:01:57,202
现在就保护我们。
Protect us now.

3
00:05:31,495 --> 00:05:36,154
莱尔德似乎在拿... ...大部分都打在他的肩膀和手肘上。
Laird seems to be taking... ... most of those blows on his shoulders and elbows.

4
00:05:37,994 --> 00:05:39,974
珀金斯的左手好像有点动。
Perkins appears to be pulling his left a bit.

5
00:05:39,998 --> 00:05:43,066
他的手可能在第二回合受伤了。
He just might have hurt that hand back in round two.

6
00:05:44,908 --> 00:05:49,197
如果你来晚了，珀金斯在第二轮数到八的时候就倒下了。
If you joined us late, Perkins was down in round two for an eight count.

7
00:05:52,166 --> 00:05:54,235
第六回合结束了。
And there's the end of round six.

8
00:06:02,294 --> 00:06:03,948
你付电话费了吗?
Did you pay the phone?

9
00:06:06,858 --> 00:06:07,985
我要借。
I gotta borrow.

10
00:06:09,347 --> 00:06:10,349
反对什么?
Against what?

11
00:06:11,178 --> 00:06:12,503
我的房子很干净。
Well, my house is clear.

12
00:06:12,527 --> 00:06:13,654
几乎。
Almost.

13
00:06:14,359 --> 00:06:15,822
没有机会。不是那栋房子。
No chance. Not that house.

14
00:06:15,846 --> 00:06:18,415
这是一个好房子。这是一栋很棒的房子。
It's a good house. It's a terrific house.

15
00:06:18,680 --> 00:06:20,107
你答应过我你会找到合适的人。
You promised me you'd find somebody.

16
00:06:20,131 --> 00:06:21,560
我说我会试试。
I said I would try.

17
00:06:22,863 --> 00:06:24,325
我得把那房子卖掉。
I gotta get rid of that house.

18
00:06:24,349 --> 00:06:25,913
那你为什么不把它给别人呢?
Well, why don't you give it to somebody?

19
00:06:25,937 --> 00:06:29,095
我试过了，那家伙说也许我可以把车扔进去。
I tried and the guy said maybe if I'd throw in my car.

20
00:06:29,119 --> 00:06:31,654
准备好支付电话费或电话答录费了吗?
Had enough ready for the phone bill or the answering service?

21
00:06:31,678 --> 00:06:33,659
这是一个好房子。但不是两者都有。
It's a good house. But not both.

22
00:06:33,683 --> 00:06:36,320
我得把它处理掉，仅此而已。所以我付了服务费。
Gotta get rid of it, that's all. So I paid the service.

23
00:06:36,344 --> 00:06:38,028
现在我们可以得到一条消息。
Now we can get a message.

24
00:06:40,111 --> 00:06:42,180
来电仍然有效。
Incoming still works.

25
00:06:43,051 --> 00:06:44,789
如果我们想喊出来呢?
What if we want to call out, you know?

26
00:06:44,813 --> 00:06:46,693
回个信息什么的?
Return a message or something?

27
00:07:05,105 --> 00:07:07,173
明天早上有个约会。
Got an appointment in the morning.

28
00:07:07,974 --> 00:07:09,177
是关于什么的?
What's it about?

29
00:07:09,806 --> 00:07:12,873
到目前为止还没有任何问题。只是个约会。
It's not about anything so far. Just an appointment.

30
00:07:13,125 --> 00:07:16,718
嗯…你可以留着它，不是吗?
Well... You can keep it, can't you?

31
00:07:17,030 --> 00:07:18,033
是的。
Yeah.

32
00:07:18,689 --> 00:07:19,692
是的。
Yeah.

33
00:07:20,107 --> 00:07:22,488
我想我今晚要去水槽里。
I'm going in the tank tonight, I think.

34
00:07:27,297 --> 00:07:28,299
是的。
Yeah.

35
00:08:32,181 --> 00:08:33,665
你知道匹兹堡的交易吗?
You know the Pittsburgh deal?

36
00:08:33,689 --> 00:08:35,096
我们放在干文件里的那个?
The one we put in the dry file?

37
00:08:35,120 --> 00:08:36,443
消失的那个?
The one that disappeared?

38
00:08:36,467 --> 00:08:37,469
是的。
Yeah.

39
00:08:38,087 --> 00:08:42,269
昨晚，我和伯尼在吃晚饭，一个男人跳着华尔兹走过来。
Well, last night, Bernie and I were having dinner, and a guy waltzes over to the table.

40
00:08:43,173 --> 00:08:45,116
然后把这个扔到我腿上。
And drops this right in my lap.

41
00:08:47,149 --> 00:08:48,277
是那个女人。
It's the woman.

42
00:08:48,359 --> 00:08:49,637
Quemando的女人。
Quemando's woman.

43
00:08:49,949 --> 00:08:52,621
她在镇上的每个围栏里都放了一个。
She's put one of those out to every fence in town.

44
00:08:52,645 --> 00:08:54,073
就像电话卡。
Like calling cards.

45
00:08:54,270 --> 00:08:56,043
她想把我们的面包卖出去。
She's trying to sell our bread.

46
00:09:02,186 --> 00:09:03,615
没有错吧?
There's no mistake?

47
00:09:04,779 --> 00:09:05,781
不。
No.

48
00:09:06,610 --> 00:09:07,613
还没有。
Not yet.

49
00:09:18,882 --> 00:09:20,567
我们找些士兵来。
Let's get some soldiers.

50
00:09:30,946 --> 00:09:32,630
希基先生还是博格斯先生?
Mr. Hickey or Mr. Boggs?

51
00:09:33,263 --> 00:09:34,265
吻痕。
Hickey.

52
00:09:36,235 --> 00:09:38,053
博格斯先生不来了?
Mr. Boggs won't be joining us?

53
00:09:38,104 --> 00:09:39,668
博格斯先生今天上午在办公室。
Mr. Boggs is in the office this morning.

54
00:09:39,692 --> 00:09:41,223
有什么能帮你的，赖斯先生?
How can we help you, Mr. Rice?

55
00:09:53,749 --> 00:09:54,751
你好。
Hello.

56
00:09:55,784 --> 00:09:56,787
是的。
Yeah.

57
00:09:57,482 --> 00:09:58,484
确定。
Sure.

58
00:09:59,318 --> 00:10:00,320
正确的。
Right.

59
00:10:01,484 --> 00:10:04,054
不，你打给蒙特，然后我们去找肥仔。
No, you call Monte, then we'll get Fatboy.

60
00:10:04,250 --> 00:10:05,253
正确的。
Right.

61
00:10:31,148 --> 00:10:33,032
尼克?我可以打电话给我妈妈吗?
Nick? Can I call my Mom?

62
00:10:33,502 --> 00:10:34,504
当然,亲爱的。
Sure, honey.

63
00:10:34,981 --> 00:10:36,924
这件事应该做得很精细。
It ought to be delicately done.

64
00:10:37,135 --> 00:10:39,579
我已经有一段时间没见到她了。
It's been some time since I've seen her.

65
00:10:40,636 --> 00:10:43,892
只要找到她，就够了。
Just to find her, is all that's really necessary.

66
00:10:44,146 --> 00:10:46,437
我不想让你联系她，明白吗?
I don't want you to contact her, you understand?

67
00:10:47,602 --> 00:10:49,031
她可能会回避。
She might shy away.

68
00:10:51,646 --> 00:10:52,648
自由裁量权。
Discretion.

69
00:10:53,168 --> 00:10:55,298
我是说，你知道这类事情。
You know the sort of thing, I mean.

70
00:10:56,589 --> 00:10:59,284
找到她在哪里，然后告诉你。
Just find out where she is and let you know.

71
00:10:59,424 --> 00:11:00,427
精确。
Precisely.

72
00:11:13,297 --> 00:11:14,337
杰克?
Jack?

73
00:11:14,361 --> 00:11:15,400
是吗?
Yeah?

74
00:11:15,474 --> 00:11:17,474
我要坐GTO;特殊的。
I'm taking the GTO; the special.

75
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,003
蒙特?
Monte?

76
00:11:20,833 --> 00:11:22,587
钥匙在遮阳板上面。
The keys are atop the visor.

77
00:11:24,255 --> 00:11:26,636
你知道这可能需要一些时间。
You understand this may take some time.

78
00:11:26,744 --> 00:11:28,807
我相信不会太久。
Well, not too very long, I trust.

79
00:11:30,373 --> 00:11:32,498
这就留下了钱的问题。
That leaves the question of money.

80
00:11:33,035 --> 00:11:35,040
每天200英镑，外加费用。
Two hundred a day plus expenses.

81
00:11:35,213 --> 00:11:36,298
我明白了。
I see.

82
00:11:36,322 --> 00:11:38,134
为通货膨胀尽自己的一份力量。
Doing your bit for inflation.

83
00:11:41,469 --> 00:11:42,998
那只是个玩笑。
It was just a joke.

84
00:11:43,751 --> 00:11:44,753
很好。
Very well.

85
00:11:45,376 --> 00:11:49,105
我的电话号码就在其中一张纸上。
My answering service number is on one of those pieces of paper.

86
00:11:49,143 --> 00:11:51,524
有消息就打给我。
Call when you have something to report.

87
00:12:00,101 --> 00:12:01,680
500美元。
Five hundred dollars.

88
00:12:02,521 --> 00:12:03,574
作为预付款。
As an advance.

89
00:12:03,939 --> 00:12:05,944
证明我的诚意。
A demonstration of my sincerity.

90
00:12:06,774 --> 00:12:08,202
这就足够了吗?
Is that sufficient?

91
00:12:11,267 --> 00:12:12,770
我想是的，赖斯先生。
I think so, Mr. Rice.

92
00:12:14,863 --> 00:12:18,206
嗯…你好，希基先生。
Well... Arrivederci, Mr. Hickey.

93
00:12:23,504 --> 00:12:25,188
我们会跟你聊的。
We'll be talking to you.

94
00:13:54,409 --> 00:13:55,664
我们的工作。
We're working.

95
00:13:55,688 --> 00:13:57,191
听你这么说我很高兴。
I'm glad to hear it.

96
00:14:02,809 --> 00:14:04,388
我不想打扰你。
I hate to bother you.

97
00:14:05,051 --> 00:14:06,815
没事，只是想休息一下。
It's all right, just wanted to take a minute.

98
00:14:06,839 --> 00:14:07,892
看到这个女孩了吗?
See this girl?

99
00:14:09,550 --> 00:14:10,874
什么，她放出去了吗?
What, does she put out?

100
00:14:10,898 --> 00:14:12,187
她是来做生意的，笨蛋。
She's business, dummy.

101
00:14:12,211 --> 00:14:14,866
玛丽·简... ...鲍尔。
Mary Jane... ...Bower.

102
00:14:14,890 --> 00:14:15,892
是的。
Yeah.

103
00:14:15,932 --> 00:14:16,936
跟我说说她吧。
Tell me about her.

104
00:14:16,960 --> 00:14:19,732
有个叫赖斯的小甜嘴想让我们找到她。
Some little sweet lips by the name of Rice wants us to find her.

105
00:14:19,756 --> 00:14:20,759
对什么?
What for?

106
00:14:20,835 --> 00:14:22,328
浪漫的联系。
A romantic connection.

107
00:14:22,352 --> 00:14:24,035
"甜唇"让人欲罢不能啊?
A switch-hitting Sweet Lips, huh?

108
00:14:24,059 --> 00:14:25,767
好吧，别取笑客户。
Yeah, well don't make fun of the client.

109
00:14:25,791 --> 00:14:27,545
我们要付5美元的定金。
We got a five bill retainer.

110
00:14:31,224 --> 00:14:33,668
你觉得钱能让我神魂颠倒吗?
Do you think money turns my head around?

111
00:15:14,779 --> 00:15:17,160
法罗，斯沃普，最后一个是什么?
Farrow, Swope and what's this last one?

112
00:15:18,167 --> 00:15:20,235
凯》。我想那是西班牙语。
Kay Mundo. That's Spanish I think.

113
00:15:22,522 --> 00:15:24,469
赖斯最后一次见到玛丽·简是什么时候?
When was the last time Rice saw Mary Jane?

114
00:15:24,493 --> 00:15:25,696
三周前。
Three weeks ago.

115
00:15:25,772 --> 00:15:28,216
我去见法罗。你去找蒂娜·斯沃普。
I'll see Farrow. You look up Tina Swope.

116
00:15:29,055 --> 00:15:30,692
他们几年前是朋友。
They were friends a few years ago.

117
00:15:30,716 --> 00:15:32,039
米饭不再喜欢它们了。
Rice don't like them anymore.

118
00:15:32,063 --> 00:15:33,456
他只想要玛丽·简。
He just wants Mary Jane.

119
00:15:33,480 --> 00:15:34,563
这是他的钱。
Well, it's his money.

120
00:15:34,587 --> 00:15:36,906
是啊，有些是我们的。
Yeah, well some of it's gonna be ours.

121
00:15:37,041 --> 00:15:41,823
听着，无论你什么时候跟这些火鸡说话，赖斯都不希望你提到他的名字。
Now, look, whenever you talk to any of these turkeys, Rice doesn't want you to mention his name.

122
00:15:42,364 --> 00:15:43,367
Nyona怎么样?
How's Nyona?

123
00:15:45,164 --> 00:15:46,167
Nyona谁?
Nyona who?

124
00:16:01,170 --> 00:16:02,854
他们是可爱的。谢谢你！
They're lovely. Thank you.

125
00:16:57,134 --> 00:17:00,153
不管是什么，我不想要，他也不想要。
Whatever it is, I don't want any, and neither does he.

126
00:17:00,177 --> 00:17:03,184
他的墨镜还没戴上，他甚至还没醒。
His shades are still down, he isn't even awake yet.

127
00:17:03,702 --> 00:17:05,387
你们这些骗子都一样。
You con-men are all alike.

128
00:17:56,523 --> 00:17:58,101
他是谁?
Who is he?

129
00:17:58,735 --> 00:18:00,542
你可以先说声"你好"
Well, you could start by saying "hello."

130
00:18:00,566 --> 00:18:01,569
你好。
Hello.

131
00:18:01,881 --> 00:18:03,342
公务员怎么样了?
How's the public servant?

132
00:18:03,366 --> 00:18:04,657
我没有时间。
I don't have time.

133
00:18:04,681 --> 00:18:05,683
他是谁?
Who is he?

134
00:18:06,581 --> 00:18:08,273
我想他的名字是法罗。
I think his name is Farrow.

135
00:18:08,898 --> 00:18:10,187
你在这里做什么?
What were you doing here?

136
00:18:10,211 --> 00:18:11,431
跳过追踪女孩。
Skip tracing a girl.

137
00:18:11,455 --> 00:18:12,458
他是个线索。
He's a lead.

138
00:18:15,224 --> 00:18:19,687
通过查看邮箱，我确定法罗先生住在1338A公寓。
By checking the mailbox I determined that Mr. Farrow lived at Apartment 1338A.

139
00:18:20,616 --> 00:18:26,260
因此，我运用了我不可思议的推理能力，走上楼梯来到了1338A公寓。
Therefore using my uncanny reasoning ability, I then proceeded up the stairs to Apartment 1338A.

140
00:18:27,115 --> 00:18:28,799
别他妈开玩笑。
No goddamn jokes.

141
00:18:29,638 --> 00:18:33,791
速记员注意，删掉希基的最后一句话和我的评论。
Note to stenographer, strike Hickey's last remark and my comment.

142
00:18:34,858 --> 00:18:36,512
实话实说吧。
Just tell it straight.

143
00:18:45,159 --> 00:18:46,162
什么吗?
Anything?

144
00:18:47,164 --> 00:18:50,514
哦，蒂娜·斯沃普很久没见过玛丽·简了。年。
Oh, Tina Swope hadn't seen Mary Jane in a long time. Years.

145
00:18:50,538 --> 00:18:52,823
他们以前和一对叫奎曼多的兄弟一起去。
They used to go with a couple of brothers named Quemando.

146
00:18:52,847 --> 00:18:55,109
玛丽·简的男朋友因持械抢劫进了监狱。
Mary Jane's boyfriend went to the can for armed robbery.

147
00:18:55,133 --> 00:18:56,928
这是一种艰难的赚钱方式。
A tough way to make a buck.

148
00:18:57,052 --> 00:18:59,939
我们明天去见另一位奎曼多先生。
So we'll go see the other Mr. Quemando tomorrow.

149
00:18:59,963 --> 00:19:00,965
是的。好吧。
Yeah. Okay.

150
00:19:01,069 --> 00:19:02,087
法罗呢?
What about Farrow?

151
00:19:02,111 --> 00:19:03,761
他被子弹夹住了。
He caught a bullet sandwich.

152
00:19:03,785 --> 00:19:06,211
你说他死了是什么意思?是的，我找到他了。
What do you mean, he's dead? Yes, I found him.

153
00:19:06,235 --> 00:19:08,105
你打算告诉我吗?
Were you gonna tell me about it?

154
00:19:08,129 --> 00:19:13,103
通过查看邮箱，我确定克利夫顿·法罗先生住在1338A公寓。
Well, by looking at the mailbox, I determined that Mr. Clifton Farrow lived in Apartment 1338A.

155
00:19:16,047 --> 00:19:17,099
发生了什么事?
What happened?

156
00:19:17,948 --> 00:19:19,632
那家伙被炸飞了。抢劫吗?
Guy got blown up. Robbery?

157
00:19:19,746 --> 00:19:21,242
看起来不像。
Doesn't look like it.

158
00:19:21,266 --> 00:19:23,040
他只是开了门，收了钱。
He just opened up his door and got paid off.

159
00:19:23,064 --> 00:19:24,492
谁拿了报纸?
Who's got the paper?

160
00:19:24,516 --> 00:19:26,201
大部分都在你桌上。
Most of it's on your desk.

161
00:19:26,245 --> 00:19:28,502
肖还有阿尔·希基的笔录。
Shaw's still got Al Hickey's transcript.

162
00:19:28,526 --> 00:19:30,218
他找到了他。希是谁?
He found him. Who's Hickey?

163
00:19:31,360 --> 00:19:33,992
他以前在霍伦贝克分部工作。
He used to be with the Hollenbeck Division.

164
00:20:17,716 --> 00:20:18,719
嗨。
Hi.

165
00:20:21,968 --> 00:20:23,741
这一点都不好笑，该死的。
That's not funny, goddamn it.

166
00:20:23,765 --> 00:20:25,770
你的幽默感真可怜。
Your sense of humor is pathetic.

167
00:20:25,909 --> 00:20:26,911
去你的。
God damn you.

168
00:20:28,536 --> 00:20:30,729
别站在那儿，给我扔条毛巾。
Don't stand there, throw me a towel.

169
00:20:46,891 --> 00:20:48,216
离开着。滚出去。
Quit gawking. Get outta here.

170
00:20:48,240 --> 00:20:49,924
在另一个房间等着。
Wait in the other room.

171
00:20:50,244 --> 00:20:51,999
我差点心脏病发作。
I almost had a heart attack.

172
00:20:52,319 --> 00:20:54,699
你觉得你做的一切都很可爱。
You think everything you do is so cute.

173
00:20:56,156 --> 00:20:59,119
这只是一种表达……在另一个房间等着。
It's just a way of saying... Just wait in the other room.

174
00:21:45,588 --> 00:21:46,791
感觉好点了吗?
You feel better?

175
00:21:50,634 --> 00:21:51,912
你想要什么?
What do you want?

176
00:21:53,123 --> 00:21:54,477
我想见你。
I want to see you.

177
00:21:55,474 --> 00:21:57,158
三周以来第一次。
First time in three weeks.

178
00:21:57,721 --> 00:21:59,011
我一直在努力工作。
I've been working very hard.

179
00:21:59,035 --> 00:22:00,037
在谁?
On who?

180
00:22:01,523 --> 00:22:03,716
别这样，亲爱的，放松点，好吗?
Come on, honey, loosen up, will you?

181
