Well, what do you need?

355
00:46:12,619 --> 00:46:14,254
那花店呢?
What about the florist?

356
00:46:14,278 --> 00:46:15,776
这是赖斯的线索。
It's a lead from Rice.

357
00:46:15,800 --> 00:46:17,400
两条线索，两个死人。
Two leads, two dead men.

358
00:46:17,424 --> 00:46:18,922
我们生活在乱世之中。
We live in troubled times.

359
00:46:18,946 --> 00:46:22,240
没错，有很多社会动荡。你找到赖斯了吗?
That's right, there's a lot of social unrest. You find Rice?

360
00:46:22,264 --> 00:46:23,519
这是下一件事。
That's the next thing.

361
00:46:23,543 --> 00:46:24,897
我们也没有。
We haven't either.

362
00:46:25,582 --> 00:46:26,976
那匹兹堡呢?
Well, what about Pittsburgh?

363
00:46:27,000 --> 00:46:33,613
去年冬天，联邦储备银行，三名警卫被杀，三枚鱼雷被杀，司机带着一袋钱跑了。
Last winter, Federal Reserve Bank, three guards killed, three torpedoes killed, driver got away with a sack of money.

364
00:46:33,637 --> 00:46:35,321
大账单。400000岁以上的老人。
Big bills. Over 400,000.

365
00:46:36,091 --> 00:46:37,969
司机被打得满身是洞。
Driver got shot full of holes.

366
00:46:37,993 --> 00:46:40,750
他们没找到钱，也没找到他女朋友。
They didn't find the money or his girlfriend.

367
00:46:41,242 --> 00:46:43,936
-她叫什么名字?-我们不知道。
- What was her name? - We don't know that.

368
00:46:46,013 --> 00:46:47,705
这有奖励吗?
Is there a reward for this?

369
00:46:53,030 --> 00:46:54,609
二万五千年。
Twenty-five thousand.

370
00:46:55,899 --> 00:46:58,092
我想从头再来一遍。
I want to go over this from the top.

371
00:46:59,597 --> 00:47:00,950
你需要什么都行。
Anything you need.

372
00:47:03,434 --> 00:47:05,753
玛丽·简弄不掉那个面团。
Mary Jane can't get rid of that dough.

373
00:47:05,958 --> 00:47:08,276
账单太大了，花不了。
The bills are too big, can't spend it.

374
00:47:08,688 --> 00:47:11,292
现在别为那个烦恼了，我们明天要去看比赛。
Don't bother with that now, we're going to the game tomorrow.

375
00:47:11,316 --> 00:47:12,820
法罗是个推销员。
Farrow was a bagman.

376
00:47:14,012 --> 00:47:21,133
她想以最低价卖掉那笔钱。我说我们要去看比赛，现在放松，享受这美好的…什么游戏?
She was trying to unload that dough at knock down rate... I said we're going to the game, now relax and enjoy this good... What game?

377
00:47:21,756 --> 00:47:22,808
公羊,猎鹰。
Rams, Falcons.

378
00:47:23,241 --> 00:47:27,069
哦,足球…我自己喜欢公羊队。
Oh, football... I favor the Rams myself.

379
00:47:27,804 --> 00:47:29,509
我以为这场比赛的票已经卖光了。
I thought the game was a sell out.

380
00:47:29,533 --> 00:47:30,535
它是。
It is.

381
00:47:31,642 --> 00:47:34,694
我们找的是玛丽·简·鲍尔，不是罗曼·加布里尔。
We're looking for Mary Jane Bower, not Roman Gabriel.

382
00:47:34,718 --> 00:47:36,536
两万五千美元。
Twenty-five thousand dollars.

383
00:47:37,657 --> 00:47:39,536
你想要多大的赔率?
What kind of odds do you want?

384
00:47:43,187 --> 00:47:44,190
公羊队?
On the Rams?

385
00:47:44,777 --> 00:47:46,907
玛丽·简去看球赛了。
On Mary Jane being at the ballgame.

386
00:47:51,760 --> 00:47:53,453
小屋,两个……
Hut, two...

387
00:49:23,418 --> 00:49:24,743
我以为她今天会来。
I thought she'd show today.

388
00:49:24,767 --> 00:49:26,120
试着制造轰动。
Try to make a hit.

389
00:49:27,877 --> 00:49:29,561
让我看看。嗯,哦。
Let me see that. Hmm, oh.

390
00:49:33,546 --> 00:49:36,081
法罗的手机旁边也写着同样的话。
Farrow had the same thing written beside his phone.

391
00:49:36,105 --> 00:49:37,789
“公羊，猎鹰，再加一个。”
"Rams, Falcons, plus one."

392
00:49:39,389 --> 00:49:41,331
还有这些座位。加1什么?
And these seats. Plus one what?

393
00:49:41,809 --> 00:49:44,064
我猜是他们勾搭的人。
Whoever they are hitting on, I guess.

394
00:49:46,163 --> 00:49:47,166
加一天?
Plus one day?

395
00:49:50,450 --> 00:49:51,578
什么,明天?
What, tomorrow?

396
00:49:53,111 --> 00:49:54,114
我不知道。
I don't know.

397
00:49:54,495 --> 00:49:56,500
他们得定个时间。
Well, they'd have to set a time.

398
00:49:58,470 --> 00:50:00,154
这张票可以打开它。
The ticket could key it.

399
00:50:01,131 --> 00:50:02,134
游戏时间。
Game time.

400
00:50:02,999 --> 00:50:04,001
这些席位。
These seats.

401
00:50:04,312 --> 00:50:05,996
加上一天。是的,很好。
Plus one day. Yeah, well.

402
00:50:12,021 --> 00:50:13,023
你好。
Hello.

403
00:50:14,544 --> 00:50:16,559
天啊，不，我不想说话。
Oh, Christ no, I don't wanna talk.

404
00:50:16,583 --> 00:50:17,636
我想睡觉。
I wanna sleep.

405
00:50:19,176 --> 00:50:22,303
你好像只在睡前记得我的电话号码。
You only seem to remember my phone number at bedtime.

406
00:50:24,603 --> 00:50:26,031
不得不在一场足球赛上工作。
Had to work at a football game.

407
00:50:26,055 --> 00:50:27,998
你应该带我去的。
Well, you should have taken me.

408
00:50:28,786 --> 00:50:31,974
当然，我们要做的任何事，都可以在棒球场做。
Sure, anything we gotta do, we can do at the ballpark.

409
00:51:06,742 --> 00:51:08,396
我再看一遍。
Let me see that again.

410
00:51:16,593 --> 00:51:19,335
像这样的贿赂只有两个人。
There's only two people in a buyoff like this.

411
00:51:19,359 --> 00:51:21,677
三个很危险。为什么是第三个座位?
Three's dangerous. Why the third seat?

412
00:51:22,850 --> 00:51:23,853
这是什么?
What is this?

413
00:51:24,924 --> 00:51:26,867
什么都没有。上面写着"伊迪丝"
Nothing. Well, it says "Edith."

414
00:51:27,309 --> 00:51:28,426
她有一部新手机。
She's got a new phone.

415
00:51:28,450 --> 00:51:30,029
你又见到她了吗?
You seeing her again?

416
00:51:30,732 --> 00:51:33,552
我不再付她赡养费了，她破产了。
I quit paying her the alimony and she's broke.

417
00:51:33,739 --> 00:51:34,867
她需要帮助。
She needs help.

418
00:51:36,090 --> 00:51:39,912
那个在韦斯特伍德有栋大房子的男朋友怎么样了?
Well, what happened to the boyfriend with the big house in Westwood?

419
00:51:40,514 --> 00:51:42,895
不管是什么，昨天就发生了。
Whatever it was, it happened yesterday.

420
00:51:44,075 --> 00:51:46,393
前一天晚上她还在那里。
She was still there the night before.

421
00:51:47,946 --> 00:51:51,774
也许她找到了更大的…有个大房子的家伙。
Well, maybe she found a bigger... Guy with a bigger house.

422
00:51:52,855 --> 00:51:53,858
不。
No.

423
00:51:55,344 --> 00:51:57,725
她一直在要求回她原来的工作。
She's been asking for her old job back.

424
00:51:58,386 --> 00:51:59,965
所以，他把她赶了出去。
So, he threw her out.

425
00:52:00,702 --> 00:52:01,992
哎呀，我想知道为什么。
Gee, I wonder why.

426
00:52:02,016 --> 00:52:03,018
好吧。
All right.

427
00:52:07,131 --> 00:52:08,815
就这一辆马车?
This the only wagon?

428
00:52:09,666 --> 00:52:10,669
好吧。
Okay.

429
00:52:13,676 --> 00:52:15,681
别把这个给丢了，好吗?
And let's not lose this one, eh?

430
00:52:25,947 --> 00:52:26,950
怎么啦？
What?

431
00:52:28,022 --> 00:52:29,706
我的房子太小了。
My house was too small.

432
00:52:30,096 --> 00:52:31,780
我知道，你告诉过我。
Yeah, I know, you told me.

433
00:55:22,217 --> 00:55:23,219
嘿!
Hey!

434
00:55:38,828 --> 00:55:40,106
好的，上士。
All right, Chief.

435
00:58:58,175 --> 00:59:00,369
我们该怎么解释?
How are we supposed to explain this?

436
00:59:02,254 --> 00:59:03,257
公羊队?
To the Rams?

437
00:59:04,639 --> 00:59:05,642
警察。
The cops.

438
00:59:08,684 --> 00:59:10,368
我会想办法的。
I'll think of something.

439
01:00:11,460 --> 01:00:13,403
谢谢，先生。祝你好运，先生。
Thank you, sir. Good luck, sir.

440
01:00:36,002 --> 01:00:38,070
越快越好，对吧。谢谢你！
Soon as you can, right. Thank you.

441
01:00:41,326 --> 01:00:42,905
我们得到了一笔奖金。
We picked up a bonus.

442
01:00:51,973 --> 01:00:53,657
他们没抓到那个女孩?
They didn't get the girl?

443
01:00:55,326 --> 01:00:56,905
女孩没有出现。
The girl didn't show.

444
01:00:58,023 --> 01:00:59,830
士兵们敲定了一笔交易。
The soldiers nailed a buy-off.

445
01:00:59,854 --> 01:01:04,704
他们把推销员烧死了所以，还是没办法查出她在和谁打交道。
They burned up the bagman so, there's still no way to find out who she's dealing with.

446
01:01:05,973 --> 01:01:07,297
我不想失去她。
I don't wanna lose her.

447
01:01:07,321 --> 01:01:08,324
继续努力。
Keep pushing.

448
01:01:08,876 --> 01:01:09,879
正确的。
Right.

449
01:01:11,608 --> 01:01:13,676
这很乱，但我们别无选择。
It's messy, but we have no choice.

450
01:01:14,442 --> 01:01:15,720
它属于我们。
It belongs to us.

451
01:01:17,484 --> 01:01:19,239
最初的股份是我们的。
The original stake was ours.

452
01:01:21,113 --> 01:01:24,679
如果我不能坚持原则，我就不能相信任何事情。
If I can't stick to a principle, I can't believe in anything.

453
01:01:24,951 --> 01:01:25,953
正确的。
Right.

454
01:01:27,820 --> 01:01:29,766
博格斯在法罗的手机旁看到了纸条。
Boggs saw the note by Farrow's phone.

455
01:01:29,790 --> 01:01:31,771
我们觉得可能会找到玛丽·简。
We figured it might lead to Mary Jane.

456
01:01:31,795 --> 01:01:34,682
我们觉得玛丽·简可能和法罗有约。
We figured Mary Jane might have had an appointment with Farrow.

457
01:01:34,706 --> 01:01:36,390
你为什么不叫我们来?
Why didn't you call us in?

458
01:01:36,600 --> 01:01:38,166
因为机会渺茫。
Cause it was a long shot.

459
01:01:38,190 --> 01:01:40,634
鱼雷是怎么发现的?
How did the torpedoes find out about it?

460
01:01:40,749 --> 01:01:42,141
他们逼出了奎曼多。
They beat it out of Quemando.

461
01:01:42,165 --> 01:01:43,663
这是什么鬼东西?
What the hell is this?

462
01:01:43,687 --> 01:01:45,692
他们知道而我们不知道?
You know, they know and we don't?

463
01:01:48,457 --> 01:01:51,026
你在体育馆打了一针，干掉了一个人。
You shoot up the Coliseum, blow off a hit.

464
01:01:51,388 --> 01:01:53,957
一个推销员死了，洛杉矶到处都是尸体。
A bagman's dead, bodies lying all over LA.

465
01:01:54,402 --> 01:01:56,288
你们两个笨蛋在大庭广众下表演。
You two bums made a grandstand play.

466
01:01:56,312 --> 01:01:58,319
你应该在外面支援我们的。
Well, you should have been out there backing us up.

467
01:01:58,343 --> 01:01:59,997
你有法罗的纸条。
You had Farrow's note.

468
01:02:00,036 --> 01:02:02,102
别闹了。你们俩瞒着我们。
Come off it. You two held out on us.

469
01:02:02,126 --> 01:02:03,818
你知道，我们也知道。
You know it and we know it.

470
01:02:03,944 --> 01:02:04,946
充电吗?
Charging us?

471
01:02:06,245 --> 01:02:07,509
我愿意......
I'd like to.

472
01:02:07,533 --> 01:02:13,046
如果我想出别的办法，我会逼你们俩的... ...你会汗流浃背的。
If I come up with anything else, I'll push you both so hard... ...you'll be sweating silver bullets.

473
01:02:13,623 --> 01:02:14,625
你听到了吗?
You hear me?

474
01:02:15,972 --> 01:02:17,326
是的，我们听到了。
Yeah, we got ears.

475
01:02:20,502 --> 01:02:22,759
如果他们把我们和酒店联系起来，我们就完了。
If they tie us to the hotel, we're done.

476
01:02:22,783 --> 01:02:23,786
是的。
Yeah.

477
01:02:24,269 --> 01:02:26,900
我们要赶在他们之前找到那个贱人。
We're gonna find that bitch before they do.

478
01:02:27,519 --> 01:02:29,524
卖鞋的，做快餐的。
Shoe salesman, short order cook.

479
01:02:29,870 --> 01:02:33,420
有许多工作向有抱负的年轻人开放。
A lot of jobs open for ambitious young men.

480
01:02:33,672 --> 01:02:35,341
你玩得很开心。不是真的。
You're having fun. Not really.

481
01:02:35,365 --> 01:02:39,155
让我看看法罗的笔记。我想查一下另外两个名字。
Let me see Farrow's note. I want to check those other two names.

482
01:02:41,553 --> 01:02:45,176
菲利普·布莱德索，埃琳娜·科尔还有括号里的"勒罗伊先生"
Philip Bledsoe, Elena Cole and in parenthesis, a "Mr. Leroy."

483
01:02:46,461 --> 01:02:48,146
只有名字，只有名字。
Just names, just names.

484
01:02:48,536 --> 01:02:50,447
那我们就从电话簿开始查。
Then we start with the phone book.

485
01:02:50,471 --> 01:02:52,156
我们得找到那个婊子。
We gotta find that bitch.

486
01:03:43,493 --> 01:03:46,338
这样等你长大了你就会知道很多东西了。
Well, that's so when you grow up you'll know a lot of stuff.

487
01:03:46,362 --> 01:03:50,035
再说了，孩子们都回学校了你一整天都要干什么?
And besides, what are you gonna do all day when the kids are back in school?

488
01:03:51,380 --> 01:03:55,815
不，我不需要秘书，但如果我需要的话，就是你了。
No, I don't need a secretary, but if I ever need one, you're it.

489
01:04:08,217 --> 01:04:09,495
我叫博格斯。
My name is Boggs.

490
01:04:10,222 --> 01:04:12,792
我想见科尔夫人。埃琳娜·科尔。
Uh, I'd like to see Mrs. Cole. Elena Cole.

491
01:04:14,025 --> 01:04:16,029
你能告诉我你想要什么吗?
Could you tell me what you want?

492
01:04:16,790 --> 01:04:20,886
我想谈谈克利夫顿·法罗和玛丽·简·鲍尔。
I want to talk about Clifton Farrow and Mary Jane Bower.

493
01:04:22,874 --> 01:04:25,068
请您在这里等一下好吗?
Would you mind waiting here, please.

494
01:04:33,556 --> 01:04:36,125
不，你下面肯定有颗牙。
No, you must have had a tooth under there.

495
01:04:36,494 --> 01:04:37,496
确定。
Sure.

496
01:04:37,773 --> 01:04:39,177
那下面肯定有颗牙。
You had to have a tooth under there.

497
01:04:39,201 --> 01:04:40,316
当然，每个人都知道。
Sure, everybody knows that.

498
01:04:40,340 --> 01:04:42,024
牙齿越多，面包就越多。
More teeth, more bread.

499
01:04:42,958 --> 01:04:46,115
你可以用棍子把他们打晕，也可以用钳子。
Well, you could knock 'em out with a stick or you could get a pair of pliers.

500
01:04:51,047 --> 01:04:52,613
不用客气，亲爱的。
You're welcome, sweetheart.

501
01:04:52,637 --> 01:04:53,840
我也爱你。
I love you, too.

502
01:04:54,400 --> 01:04:56,588
但我不能说出来，因为太尴尬了。
Except I can't say it cause it's embarrassing.

503
01:04:56,612 --> 01:04:58,617
你能让你妈妈给我打电话吗?
Will you ask your Mom to call me?

504
01:04:58,790 --> 01:05:00,293
是的。请乖一点。
Yes. Please be good.

505
01:05:01,279 --> 01:05:02,963
好吧，挂电话，亲爱的。
All right, hang up, dear.

506
01:05:03,007 --> 01:05:04,511
好吧，再见。
All right, bye, bye.

507
01:05:38,336 --> 01:05:39,339
你好。
Hello.

508
01:05:42,864 --> 01:05:44,443
请这边走。
Step this way please.

509
01:06:48,543 --> 01:06:49,545
伯格斯吗?
Boggs?

510
01:06:51,032 --> 01:06:53,476
你这是什么名字啊，兄弟?
Now, what kind of name is that, brother?

511
01:06:54,040 --> 01:06:55,042
爱尔兰人。
Irish.

512
01:06:55,353 --> 01:06:56,355
黑色的爱尔兰?
Black Irish?

513
01:06:57,876 --> 01:06:58,878
主要是。
Mostly.

514
01:06:59,639 --> 01:07:00,642
好吧。
All right.

515
01:07:01,852 --> 01:07:03,536
莱斯特。给他拿把椅子。
Lester. Get him a chair.

516
01:07:12,844 --> 01:07:13,846
待在家里。
Be at home.

517
01:07:16,335 --> 01:07:18,020
啊，去吧，待在家里。
Ah, go ahead, be at home.

518
01:07:22,316 --> 01:07:24,008
我能为你做什么?
Now, what can I do for you?

519
01:07:28,538 --> 01:07:31,045
好吧?都在角落里排队。对吧?
Okay? All lined up for the corner. Right?

520
01:07:32,272 --> 01:07:33,964
保持放松。真是个好女孩。
Keep loose there. Atta girl.

521
01:07:34,933 --> 01:07:35,936
现在。
Now.

522
01:07:36,592 --> 01:07:38,276
她想做生意。
She wants to do business.

523
01:07:38,425 --> 01:07:39,427
什么时候?
When?

524
01:07:39,566 --> 01:07:40,568
今晚。
Tonight.

525
01:07:42,400 --> 01:07:43,603
叫部队来。
Call the troops.

526
01:07:57,298 --> 01:07:59,303
你还挺冷静的。
You're taking things pretty calm.

527
01:08:00,202 --> 01:08:01,781
是的。什么发生?
Yeah. Anything happen?

528
01:08:04,765 --> 01:08:06,449
我找不到布莱索。
I couldn't find Bledsoe.

529
01:08:07,461 --> 01:08:09,145
我撞到了科尔夫人。
Uh, I ran down Mrs. Cole.

530
01:08:11,368 --> 01:08:12,646
她有什么故事?
What's her story?

